ENTRY       EC 3.5.1.102                Enzyme
NAME        2-amino-5-formylamino-6-ribosylaminopyrimidin-4(3H)-one 5'-monophosphate deformylase;
            ArfB
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
            In linear amides
SYSNAME     2-amino-5-formylamino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one amidohydrolase
REACTION    2-amino-5-formylamino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one + H2O = 2,5-diamino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one + formate [RN:R09374]
ALL_REAC    R09374
SUBSTRATE   2-amino-5-formylamino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one [CPD:C15563];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     2,5-diamino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one [CPD:C01304];
            formate [CPD:C00058]
COMMENT     The enzyme catalyses the second step in archaeal riboflavin and 7,8-didemethyl-8-hydroxy-5-deazariboflavin biosynthesis. The first step is catalysed by EC 3.5.4.29 (GTP cyclohydrolase IIa). The bacterial enzyme, EC 3.5.4.25 (GTP cyclohydrolase II) catalyses both reactions.
